section arc_afternoon
title What the house did after the morning fold
p Teacher ai-jail v1.12.0 installed under gitignored tools/.cache/bin; AIJAIL_BIN in personal enclosure.conf; gratitude study submodule at v1.12.0. Commit c57bb00.
p Launch-cursor Rishi path prepared: --extract · UndefinedName image fix · if-then-assert-else parse fix · invoke cursor-jail with bash not dash. Commits 1988093 7e9a44d cf0558a.
p Host on-path G0-complete GREEN on Framework sitting 140403: Phase A nographic serial saw GRUB loading; Phase B -display none + QMP PNG; refuse-probe restored. Caller LANE_KVM=true wins over conf. Heartbeats to /dev/tty; grep -aFq not rg under Rishi PATH. Seated 065b6ab. Commits bc8eff6 4067b0a 4dd8c99 6f07540 065b6ab.
p Same-sitting metal parity granted earlier; host tee began. First RED at Tally maybe — build without RYE_ZIG under narrow PATH. Pin e7a0593. Orchestrator print ch.out on fail + tee recipe 0d75c1b.
p Second RED class at align_session_logs — same missing RYE_ZIG. Kaeden asked whether Rishi must use bash then whether sh is required at all for Linux. Answer: run is argv-direct via std.process.run; sh is convenience; RYE_ZIG via run ["env" "RYE_ZIG=…" …]. GREEN from Rye tools is std.debug.print → assert .err not .out.
p kg restyled tally_maybe no_padding parse_int align_session_logs tame_usize_audit enrich_strengthening_docs comlink_device_wire to argv-direct; parity_ch01 nested prints out+err. Six witnesses GREEN in jail. go ff35220 pushed four remotes while host tee still running.

