section rishi_shell_law_seated_in_chat
title Kaeden Q&A seated for Claude eyes
p Do Rishi scripts have to rely on bash? No. ~338 sh vs ~10 bash. Bash only for real bashisms (Ubuntu dash rejects pipefail).
p Do we have to use sh at all — is that the Linux syscall path? No. run ["cmd" "arg"] → std.process.run argv → execve lineage. File I/O via read-file write-file list-dir. sh -c is host convenience for compounds/env/pipes.
p Preferred pin form: run ["mkdir" "-p" "dir"] then run ["env" "RYE_ZIG=${zig}" "rye/bin/rye" "build" …]. Assert tool GREEN on .err when the tool uses std.debug.print.
p Growing native run-environ or mkdir builtins awaits Claude ruling — not opened this sitting.

